<a href="http://www.wikiceleb.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.wikiceleb.com</a>";s:10:"post_title";s:40:"Egypt Road to Russia FIFA World Cup 2018";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:37:"egypt-road-russia-fifa-world-cup-2018";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2018-01-22 23:55:51";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2018-01-22 18:10:51";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:27:"http://wikiceleb.com/?p=493";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"1";}i:9;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"503";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2017-12-22 12:08:25";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2017-12-22 06:23:25";s:12:"post_content";s:6416:"<p style="text-align: justify;">The South American nation Colombia, currently ranked 13<sup>th</sup> in the FIFA World Rankings. Colombia has managed to appear 6 times in a FIFA World Cup, including 2018 World Cup hosting by Russia. Colombia was selected to play this prestigious tournament in the year 1962, 1990, 1994, 1998, and 2014. Colombia had its strongest period during the 1990s.Colombia is known for having a passionate fan base. In 1990, Cameroon won the game 2-1 in extra time, thereby eliminating Colombia. In 1994 FIFA World Cup, Colombia finished top of the table in their group without having a single match lost included a historic and memorable 5-0 win over <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/argentina-russia-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Argentina</a>, which began a special mutual respect rivalry between both countries. In 1998 FIFA World Cup, Colombia was assigned to group G with the nations England, Romania and Tunisia. During the tournament, Colombia only earned one win against Tunisia and suffered two losses against England and Romania, which eliminate them in the group stage. In 2002 FIFA World Cup, Colombia failing to qualify due to goal difference against <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/uruguay-road-russia-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Uruguay</a> andÂ  Colombia did not qualify for FIFA World Cup 2006 and 2010.In 2014 FIFA World Cup, Colombia fell to host nation Brazil 2-1 in the Quarter-final round, having James Rodriguez as the World Cupâ€™s leading goal scorer and Juan Cuadrado as an assist leader.</p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-504" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/colombia-national-football-team-â€“-predictions-2014-fifa-world-cup-brazil1-300x193.jpg" alt="" width="532" height="342" />

<strong><u>World Cup Qualifier South America</u></strong>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Colombia played a total of 18 games for their Qualifying round in South America with a total of 27 points on the table conceding 7 wins 6 draws and 5 losses. Colombia drew 1- 1 against Peru in the first round of World Cup qualifier and defeated 1-2 against Paraguay in the second round. In the third round, Colombia again drewÂ Â  1-1 against <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/brazil-road-russia-fifa-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Brazil</a> and again in fourth round they consecutively drew 0-0 against Venezuela. Colombia earned six points after back to back victory over 0-2 over Ecuador and 1-0 against Bolivia. But in the seventh round, Colombia defeated 3-0 against rivalry nation <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/argentina-russia-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Argentina</a>. Colombia drew 0-0 against Chile and 2-2 against <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/uruguay-road-russia-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Uruguay</a> in 8<sup>th</sup> and 9<sup>th</sup> round respectively. In 10<sup>th</sup> round Colombia win 0- over Paraguay and defeated 2-1 against <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/brazil-road-russia-fifa-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Brazil</a> in the 11<sup>th</sup> round of World Cup qualifying. Then Colombia won back to back three matches 2-0 against Venezuela, 3-1 against Ecuador and 2-3 against Bolivia, in 12<sup>th</sup>, 13<sup>th</sup>, and 14<sup>th</sup> round of World Cup qualifying round respectively. Again Colombia loses 0-1 against <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/argentina-russia-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Argentina</a> in the 15<sup>th</sup> round and drew 1-1 against Chile in the 16<sup>th</sup> round. In the 17<sup>th</sup> round of World Cup qualifying Colombia loses 3-0 against <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/uruguay-road-russia-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Uruguay</a> and at last round of World Cup qualifying match Colombian team managed to score a brace against <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/peru-road-russia-fifa-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Peru</a> and qualified for the FIFA World Cup 2018, <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/russia-host-fifa-world-cup-2018/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Russia</a>.</p>
<img class="aligncenter wp-image-505" src="http://wikiceleb.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/colombia-celebration-300x170.jpg" alt="" width="535" height="303" />

